 statement of Rawls's view, much of the extensive literature on his theory refers to the original. This first edition is available for scholars and serious students of Rawls's work.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Sep 2020) 0aJustice. 0aPHILOSOPHYxPolitical. 0aPhilosophy. 0aRechtvaardigheid. 0aSocial Justice. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999z978311044221240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674042605423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780674042605.jpg  a978-3-11-044221-2  HUP eBook Package Archive 1896-2004c1893d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK